import cv2
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def read_and_display_image(file_path):
    img_rgb = cv2.imread(file_path, cv2.IMREAD_COLOR)
    img_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(img_rgb, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)

    plt.imshow(img_rgb)
    plt.title('Original RGB Image')
    plt.show()

    return img_rgb

def plot_histogram(image, title='Histogram'):
    colors = ('b', 'g', 'r')

    for i, col in enumerate(colors):
        hist = cv2.calcHist([image], [i], None, [256], [0, 256])
        plt.plot(hist, color=col)
        plt.xlim([0, 256])

    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

def negative_transform(image):
    neg_transformed_img = 255 - image
    plt.imshow(neg_transformed_img)
    plt.title('Negative Transformed RGB Image')
    plt.show()

    return neg_transformed_img

def main():
    file_path = 'img/sky.jpg'
    original_image = read_and_display_image(file_path)

    plot_histogram(original_image, title='Histogram of Original Image')

    neg_transformed_image = negative_transform(original_image)

    plot_histogram(neg_transformed_image, title='Histogram of Negative Transformed Image')

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def read_and_display_image(file_path):
    image = cv2.imread(file_path)
    image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    plt.imshow(image_rgb)
    plt.title('Original RGB Image')
    plt.show()
    return image_rgb

def log_transform(image_rgb):
    epsilon = 1e-8
    c_value = 255 / np.log(1 + np.max(image_rgb) + epsilon)
    log_transformed_image = c_value * (np.log(image_rgb + epsilon))
    log_transformed_image = np.nan_to_num(log_transformed_image)
    log_transformed_image = np.array(log_transformed_image, dtype=np.uint8)
    return log_transformed_image

def display_image(image, title):
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.title(title)
    plt.show()

def main():
    #     
    file_path = 'img/sky.jpg'
    original_image_rgb = read_and_display_image(file_path)

    #     
    log_transformed_image = log_transform(original_image_rgb)
    display_image(log_transformed_image, title='Log Transformed RGB Image')

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def read_and_display_image(file_path):
    image = cv2.imread(file_path)
    image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    return image_rgb

def gamma_correction(image_rgb, gamma_value):
    # -
    gamma_corrected_image = np.power(image_rgb / 255.0, gamma_value)
    gamma_corrected_image = np.uint8(gamma_corrected_image * 255.0)
    return gamma_corrected_image

def display_images(original_image, corrected_image, gamma_value):
    #    - 
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))

    axes[0].imshow(original_image)
    axes[0].set_title('Original RGB Image')

    axes[1].imshow(corrected_image)
    axes[1].set_title(f'Gamma-Corrected (Gamma = {gamma_value})')

    plt.show()

def main():
    #     
    file_path = 'img/sky.jpg'
    original_image_rgb = read_and_display_image(file_path)

    # -   
    gamma_value = 2
    gamma_corrected_image = gamma_correction(original_image_rgb, gamma_value)
    display_images(original_image_rgb, gamma_corrected_image, gamma_value)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def read_and_display_image(file_path):
    image = cv2.imread(file_path)
    image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    return image_rgb

def solarize_image(image, threshold_value):
    blue, green, red = cv2.split(image)

    #   
    solarized_blue = np.where(blue < threshold_value, blue, 255 - blue)
    solarized_green = np.where(green < threshold_value, green, 255 - green)
    solarized_red = np.where(red < threshold_value, red, 255 - red)

    #      
    solarized_image = cv2.merge((solarized_blue, solarized_green, solarized_red))
    return solarized_image

def display_images(original_image, solarized_image):
    #     
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(original_image)
    plt.title('Original Image')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(solarized_image)
    plt.title('Solarized Image')

    plt.show()

def main():
    #     
    file_path = 'img/sky.jpg'
    original_image_rgb = read_and_display_image(file_path)

    #    
    threshold_value = 128
    solarized_image = solarize_image(original_image_rgb, threshold_value)
    display_images(original_image_rgb, solarized_image)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def read_and_display_image(file_path):
    image = cv2.imread(file_path)
    image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
    return image_rgb

def equalize_image(image):
    #  
    blue, green, red = cv2.split(image)

    #     
    equalized_blue = cv2.equalizeHist(blue)
    equalized_green = cv2.equalizeHist(green)
    equalized_red = cv2.equalizeHist(red)

    #      
    equalized_image = cv2.merge((equalized_blue, equalized_green, equalized_red))
    return equalized_image

def display_images(original_image, equalized_image):
    #     
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(original_image)
    plt.title('Original Image')

    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.imshow(equalized_image)
    plt.title('Equalized Image')

    plt.show()

def main():
    #     
    file_path = 'img/sky.jpg'
    original_image_rgb = read_and_display_image(file_path)

    #    
    equalized_image = equalize_image(original_image_rgb)
    display_images(original_image_rgb, equalized_image)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def read_and_display_image(file_path):
    image = cv2.imread(file_path)
    return image

def calculate_and_plot_histogram(channel, color, title):
    hist = cv2.calcHist([channel], [0], None, [256], [0, 256])
    plt.plot(hist, color=color)
    plt.title(title)

def display_histograms(image):
    b, g, r = cv2.split(image)

    #      
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

    plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)
    calculate_and_plot_histogram(b, 'blue', 'Histogram for Channel B')

    plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)
    calculate_and_plot_histogram(g, 'green', 'Histogram for Channel G')

    plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)
    calculate_and_plot_histogram(r, 'red', 'Histogram for Channel R')

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def main():
    #    
    file_path = 'img/sky.jpg'
    image = read_and_display_image(file_path)

    #    
    display_histograms(image)

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
